Assistant Legal Counsel Job (Banking), Jakarta, Indonesia - PT Monroe Consulting Group
Assistant Legal Counsel Job (Banking), Jakarta, Indonesia  -
Assistant Legal Counsel Job (Banking), Jakarta, Indonesia
Responsibilities
Monroe Consulting Group is currently recruiting on behalf of one of the world’s leading money transfer companies. Our respected client is seeking an experienced legal counsel to fill the job of Assistant Legal Counsel. This job will be based in Jakarta, Indonesia. The position demands a quality candidate with extensive experience in all aspects of the law, compliance and litigation. The winning candidate will be responsible for providing corporate, regulatory and commercial legal advice across multiple authorities to designated Emerging Markets business development teams and corporate business units, with a main focus on Asean.Key job responsibilities: Assist in the provision of general corporate and commercial legal and regulatory advice across the Emerging Markets to support the line managerContribute in the negotiation, drafting and amendment of standard agreements for potential agents in the designated territory (Middle East, South Asia and Asia Pacific) in conjunction with relevant business teamsAssist in the review and negotiation of all other contractual arrangementsAdvice the business on legal and regulatory matters, in conjunction with local counsel related to the provision of company’s services in each of its applicable jurisdictions.Assist with all due respect to the management of the Indonesian subsidiary, regulated by Bank Indonesia.Obtain advice, perform research and draft memoranda on legal aspects in terms of new products and the development of new distribution channelsEducate and manager outside counsel in various international authorities as directed by line managerCollaborate closely with the Compliance department in ensuring that the provision of services is made according to Anti-Money Laundering requirementsAssist with the management of any litigation processes and liaise with outside counsel as requiredAssist with mergers, acquisitions, and divestitures and related integration processes Job Requirements  Bachelor’s degree (minimum)Five years’ experience (minimum) in corporate law, preferably with legal or financial institutionProven track record in legal-contractual drafting with a deep understanding in infrastructure projects (project finance)In-depth knowledge of Indonesia’s laws and regulations, as well as foreign-international laws and regulationsAbility to multitask and work under tight schedules with attention to detailExcellent communication skills (able to communicate throughout all channels/levels)Good organization and management skillsGood work ethics and excellent leadership skillsFirst class interpersonal skillsStrong oral and written both in Indonesian and English with vast experience in documentation All applications will be treated in the strictest of confidence. If you are a suitable match for this position please send your application to banking@monroeconsulting.com
